<br>
If you don't have the staff, I would highly suggest doing the quest.  I would also invest in SoW potions if you are not already.  Quadding becomes so much easier with these two items.<br>
<br>
You pull your mobs with the staff.  Don't even try to BoF them until you have all your mobs and have them all tightly packed.  Once you have 2 or 3 or 4... however many you are doing, run circles around them until they all bunch up.  Once they do, sprint out a ways and then hit them with BoF.  If one resists, run out and BoF that one that resisted, circle to get them all back together again, and cast BoF again.  Watch for it to hit all 4.<br>
<br>
When you get all of them snared at the same time, you should be able to finish off the quad without BoF ever wearing off.  If you get resists or it is taking a long time or you simply like being cautious, simply resnare at some point. <p>Gelad Mystichord- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=190995" target="top">Gelad's Ghetto Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
