Re: BOF breaking at random.<br>
<br>
Unless you are pulling with BOF, then one shouldn't just break snare all of a sudden.   BOF has a fixed duration.<br>
<br>
It can be frustrating to have one or two resist bonds, but all you need to do is keep running straight until you have distance and retry BOF on the one(s) who resisted.  Then, just round them all up again and reapply BOF before you start to nuke em down.  The great thing about KEI is that your mana will keep going up even while you are taking time to deal with a resist.<br>
<br>
If only one of them resist, then you can root it, apply bonds and nuke with a very low level, fast casting nuke to break root.  Round em up again and reapply BOF as before.  <br>
<br>
I seem to recall that until I got the hang of the timing on those dwarves, I reapplied BOF after about 5 or 6 casts.  After a while, you will get more efficient (less 'too far away from target' time) and can do them with one BOF.  <br>
<br>
I liked the shore dorf camp better than the docks, for some reason.<br>
