<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/graffe1.0/quests/StaffofTemperateFlux/stafftemperateflux.htm#popdown" target="top">Staff of Temperate Flux Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
It has many uses some of which are:<br>
<br>
Lower Element - The effect itself lowers a mobs fire and cold resists by 6 making nuking them that much easier<br>
<br>
Instant Aggro - Target a mob, click the staff and he'll come chasing after you.  No need to waste mana on a spell to pull<br>
<br>
Faction Tagging - Just flux a mob that another group is fighting and you will get faction when it dies<br>
<br>
Gem refresh - Cast a nuke, click ur flux staff (or an instant clicky) and your gems will refresh meaning you can cast your next nuke faster<br>
<br>
Distance checker - When things go wrong and you have an unsnared mob chasing after you, you can hit your flux staff to judge how far away he is.  IE If you see the message &quot;Target is uncomfortable&quot;  you are pretty close.  If you see no message at all, then about mid range.  And if you see &quot;Target is out of range&quot; then you might just have enough room to get off a new snare or root.<br>
<br>
Spamming - Great for annoying your friends when you target them and click away.<br>
<br>
The staff can be used from your inventory and shouldn't be too hard for you to get at your level especially if a group is camping the bar in SolA.  Good luck getting it and my only advice on quadding is to make sure you resnare once you have all 4 of the mobs together.  That way snare will not break at different times.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://students.cs.tamu.edu/dgm4987/aura3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tsurok@graffeswizardcompilation>Tsurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/03 12:19:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25585.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: alright</span><hr size=1> Wiz quading is a bit different than druid quading in that our snare is MUCH shorter duration than theirs and an AOE.  So, druids will snare prior to rounding them up for nuuking.  Wizards pull with either the flux staff, fast casting nuke, or proximity aggro if KOS.  Run them around at full speed (hence the need for jboots/sow potions), head straight to gain distance, then cast BOF.<br>
<br>
In addition to pulling, the flux staff helps determine casting distance and is especially nice on the initial snare.  Spam the staff on one of the mobs until you get the OOR message, which lets you know, in most cases, that you have enough distance to cast BOF (and not snare yourself, which is important).<br>
